text: Silcott is an unincorporated community in Asotin County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Silcott was established in 1883, and remained in operation until 1931. The community was named after John Silcott, an early settler. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Asotin County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Silcott, Washington
